-- CANADA RESEARCH ROUNDUP-BlackBerry, Kinross, Glacier Media Inc 
-- 
-- Mon Mar 31, 2014 07:36AM EDT
-- None



31 March (Reuters) - Securities analysts revised their ratings and price targets on several Canadian companies, including BlackBerry and Kinross, on Monday.

HIGHLIGHTS * BlackBerry <BB.TO>: Canaccord Genuity, UBS raises target price  * Kinross Gold Corp <K.TO>: RBC cuts target price to $7 from $7.50 * Glacier Media Inc <GVC.TO>: Canaccord Genuity raises to buy from hold rating   Following is a summary of research actions on Canadian companies reported by Reuters on Monday. Stock entries are in alphabetical order.* BlackBerry <BB.TO>: Canaccord Genuity raises target price to $8 from $6; rating hold * BlackBerry <BB.TO>: Evercore cuts to underweight from equal-weight rating  * BlackBerry <BB.TO>: Evercore cuts target price to $6 from $7 * BlackBerry <BB.TO>: UBS raises target price to $8.50 from $8; ratingneutral * BRP Inc <DOO.TO>: Canaccord Genuity raises target price to C$35 from C$34; rating buy * Donnycreek Energy <DCK.V>: NBF cuts target price to C$3.50 from C$4; rating outperform * Glacier Media Inc <GVC.TO>: Canaccord Genuity raises to buy from hold rating  * Glacier Media Inc <GVC.TO>: Canaccord Genuity raises target price to C$1.80 * Golden Queen Mining Co Ltd <GQM.TO>: Canaccord Genuity raises target to C$1.65; hold * IBI Group Inc <IBG.TO>: Canaccord Genuity raises to hold from sell rating  * IBI Group Inc <IBG.TO>: Canaccord Genuity raises target price to C$1.50 from C$0.75 * Kinross Gold Corp <K.TO>: RBC cuts target price to $7 from $7.50; rating outperform * Nordion Inc <NDN.TO>: CIBC raises target to C$13 from C$11.50; sector underperformer